<section>
    <h2>Participate in an RFC</h2>
    <p>
        RFC stands for Request for Comments, the process that Ember follows to get community input on proposed features. 
        All Ember users are invited to comment on RFCs with their thoughts and opinions,
        as well as write RFCs of their own!
        Once an RFC is merged, that means it has been given the green flag for the feature
        to be built and shipped. That process could take months or years after an RFC is merged.
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/emberjs/rfcs/pulls">RFCs that need comments</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://emberjs.github.io/rfcs/">Accepted RFCs</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/emberjs/rfc-tracking">Tracking feature implementation</a></li>
    </ul>
</section>

